âª That the Yanks are coming... âª

17:45.260 --> 17:46.960
( <i>blast of heavy metal music )
Ahh!</i>

17:49.330 --> 17:53.100
Okay, fish, you're probably
wondering why I'm still here.

17:53.170 --> 17:54.540
Catching you

17:54.600 --> 17:57.730
will make me the most famous
fisherman there is

17:57.810 --> 18:00.180
right up there with...
the, uh...

18:00.240 --> 18:03.150
the bald guy
on the cable fishing show.

18:03.210 --> 18:04.550
Whoa!

18:06.250 --> 18:07.180
Holy mackerel!

18:09.420 --> 18:11.860
Milhouse,
didn't see you, pal.
Look out, my man.

18:11.920 --> 18:14.530
Cherry party Bart.
Any chicks over eight?

18:14.590 --> 18:16.060
Not yet, but
the afternoon is young.

18:19.190 --> 18:21.120
Lisa, what's wrong?

18:21.200 --> 18:23.070
Isn't it obvious?
We've degraded ourselves

18:23.130 --> 18:26.870
and set back the
children's rights movement
for decades to come.

18:26.930 --> 18:28.400
You're great
at a party, Lise.
Really great.

18:28.470 --> 18:29.410
Hey, you! Don't!

18:29.470 --> 18:30.440
Shut that door!

18:30.510 --> 18:31.510
Stop it!

18:31.570 --> 18:32.530
Put that away!

18:32.610 --> 18:33.540
No! Stop!

18:33.610 --> 18:35.050
Oh!

18:35.110 --> 18:36.250
Ow!

18:36.310 --> 18:37.350
( <i>laughing )</i>

18:37.410 --> 18:38.820
You young hellion.

18:38.880 --> 18:40.850
You want me
to take off my belt?

18:40.920 --> 18:41.890
Yeah.

18:41.950 --> 18:43.020
I'll show you.

18:43.080 --> 18:43.940
( <i>laughing )</i>

18:44.020 --> 18:45.060
Doggone it.

18:45.120 --> 18:46.590
( <i>grunting )</i>

18:46.650 --> 18:48.280
I love you

18:48.360 --> 18:50.260
but I must kill you.

18:55.500 --> 18:56.770
Thanks for coming.

18:56.830 --> 18:57.970
Nice tie, Nelson.

18:58.030 --> 19:00.430
Thanks. It's your dad's.

19:00.500 --> 19:03.610
( <i>crying: )
I tried to be a good baby-sitter</i>

19:03.670 --> 19:05.210
but I failed.

19:05.270 --> 19:08.840
I'm a feeb--
a useless, old, worn-down...

19:08.910 --> 19:13.350
( <i>crying )</i>

19:13.410 --> 19:15.580
Lisa, I have this
strong unpleasant feeling

19:15.650 --> 19:16.850
I've never had before.

19:16.920 --> 19:18.560
It's called remorse

19:18.620 --> 19:20.260
you vile burlesque
of irrepressible youth.

19:20.320 --> 19:21.930
How do you make this
feeling go away?

19:21.990 --> 19:23.460
You grab a bucket and a brush

19:23.520 --> 19:26.120
and you clean harder and faster
than you ever have before.

19:26.190 --> 19:28.120
( <i>crying )</i>

19:28.200 --> 19:29.130
( <i>door slams )</i>

19:29.200 --> 19:32.140
( <i>laughing )</i>

19:34.440 --> 19:37.870
