19:39.410 --> 19:41.780
âª No time for losers âª

19:41.840 --> 19:47.240
âª 'Cause I am the champions
of the world! âª

19:47.320 --> 19:50.150
Uh-oh.

19:50.220 --> 19:51.390
Hi, honey.

19:51.450 --> 19:54.210
Uh... how's the marriage
retreat going?

19:54.290 --> 19:55.660
We came to this retreat

19:55.720 --> 19:57.720
because I thought
our marriage was in trouble.

19:57.790 --> 20:00.460
But I never thought
for a minute that it was
in this much trouble.

20:00.530 --> 20:01.670
Homer, how can you expect--

20:01.730 --> 20:03.670
Marge, you don't know
what this fish means.

20:03.730 --> 20:05.700
This fish represents a better
life for both of us.

20:05.770 --> 20:07.900
This fish makes me
a champion and a hero.

20:07.970 --> 20:08.940
To who?

20:09.000 --> 20:09.930
To those weirdos

20:10.000 --> 20:11.400
in the worm store.

20:11.470 --> 20:13.530
All this fish represents
is just how selfish you are.

20:13.610 --> 20:16.010
Well if that's the way you feel,
I'll throw it back.

20:16.080 --> 20:17.050
Oh, yeah, sure.

20:17.110 --> 20:18.120
Watch!

20:18.180 --> 20:19.280
( <i>grunting )</i>

20:20.780 --> 20:24.420
Wow, I did it.

20:24.490 --> 20:26.290
I gave up
fame and breakfast

20:26.350 --> 20:27.950
for my marriage.

20:28.020 --> 20:29.850
I fought it
for six hours.

20:29.920 --> 20:30.880
<i>She says one word</i>

20:30.960 --> 20:32.760
<i>and I toss it back.</i>

20:32.830 --> 20:36.000
And you're telling me
our marriage is in trouble?

20:36.060 --> 20:37.720
Come here, baby.

20:37.800 --> 20:41.140
Oh, Homer.

20:42.970 --> 20:46.080
( <i>grunting )</i>

20:46.140 --> 20:47.710
( <i>grunting )</i>

20:49.110 --> 20:51.550
Eww.

20:51.610 --> 20:53.070
Eww.

20:53.150 --> 20:54.250
Mmm.

21:03.060 --> 21:04.060
We're back.

21:04.130 --> 21:05.060
How's your
marriage?

21:05.130 --> 21:08.200
Same as usual--
perfectomundo.

21:08.260 --> 21:10.060
Oh my, the house
looks wonderful.

21:10.130 --> 21:11.940
Grandpa, what's your secret?

21:12.000 --> 21:13.500
Pretending to cry.

21:13.570 --> 21:15.170
( <i>laughing )</i>

21:15.240 --> 21:17.070
That's right,
you heard me!

21:17.140 --> 21:18.680
Pretending to cry!

21:18.740 --> 21:22.110
I can turn it on and off
like a faucet.

21:22.180 --> 21:23.350
( <i>crying )</i>

21:23.410 --> 21:25.750
Oh, I'm crying. I'm so sad.

21:25.810 --> 21:26.970
Way to go, Grampa.

21:27.050 --> 21:29.590
I'll never trust
another old person.

21:29.650 --> 21:30.920
I fooled you.

21:30.990 --> 21:32.490
So long, suckers.

21:32.550 --> 21:33.750
( <i>chuckling )</i>

21:33.820 --> 21:35.990
Yeah. General Sherman.

21:36.060 --> 21:39.330
They say he's 500 pounds
of bottom-dwelling fury.

21:39.390 --> 21:41.090
No one knows
how old he is

21:41.160 --> 21:42.570
but if you ask me,
and most people do,

21:42.630 --> 21:43.830
he's a hundred years
if he's a day.

21:43.900 --> 21:45.440
No one's ever
caught him?

21:45.500 --> 21:47.000
One fella
came close.

21:47.070 --> 21:48.810
<i>Went by the name
of Homer.</i>

21:48.870 --> 21:51.980
<i>Seven feet tall, he was,
with arms like tree trunks</i>

21:52.040 --> 21:53.810
<i>and his eyes
were like steel:
cold and hard.</i>

21:53.880 --> 21:55.480
<i>Had a shock of hair--</i>

21:55.540 --> 21:56.740
<i>red, like the fires of hell.</i>
